      "histoire.hero.title": "WHEN TIME <br>BECOMES ART",
      "histoire.title": "DA VINCI",
      "histoire.hero.desc": "Our brand was born from a dream‚Ä¶",
      "histoire.hero.cta": "Learn more",
      "histoire.section1.title": "Where Time <br>and Art Were Born",
      "histoire.section2.title": "The Visionary Who <br>Saw More Than Time",
      "histoire.section3.title": "The Birth <br>of a Legacy",
      "histoire.section4.title": "Three Centuries of Craft, One Unchanged Soul",
      "histoire.section5.title": "A Sensory Journey <br>Between Painting and Watchmaking",
      "histoire.section6.title": "Enter the Da Vinci <br>Universe",
      "histoire.section1.text": "It all begins in the small Italian city of Florence, in 1674, at the heart of a workshop where the scent of linseed oil blended with freshly carved wood.<BR><BR>There the founding idea of DA VINCI was born, creator of handcrafted luxury watches: to unite the poetry of master paintings with the precision of the first watchmaking mechanisms.<BR><BR>Each watch in the DA VINCI collection pays tribute to art and prestigious watchmaking, offering enthusiasts a unique experience where art meets high‚Äëprecision horology.",
      "histoire.section2.text": "Lorenzo Da Verdi (1651‚Äì1712) was a discreet yet remarkable painter, known for his meticulous work and his ability to capture light as if he were trying to understand time itself.<br><br>During his travels across Europe, between German watchmakers‚Äô workshops and Florentine galleries, he developed a bold idea:<br><br>‚ÄúIf the brush captures the instant, then a watch can preserve its soul.‚Äù ‚Äî Lorenzo Da Verdi<br><br>In 1683 he founded the first manufatura d‚Äôarte e tempo, a workshop where painters, engravers, and watchmakers collaborated to create unique pieces.<br>His first watches were not sold: he offered them to patrons and travelers inspired by his vision.<br><br>Thus was born a tradition where each creation became a fragment of history, passed down from generation to generation.",
      "histoire.section3.text": "Over the centuries, the small manufacture crossed eras:<br>from baroque to late Renaissance, from mechanical revolutions to the industrial age.<br>Always guided by a singular philosophy: honoring the beauty of the past while adapting it to the future.<br><br>In the 19th century, under the direction of Da Verdi‚Äôs descendants, the workshop officially took the name Da Vinci Arte & Tempo, in tribute to its artistic influence and the mechanical precision of its creations.<br><br>During European modernization, the manufacture adopted more technical tools while preserving a nearly sacred hand‚Äëcrafted work:<br>cold engraving, hand‚Äëpainted dials, crowns shaped in the ancestral workshop.<br><br>Even today, our artisans perpetuate this ritual, the direct heir of more than three centuries of craftsmanship.",
      "histoire.section4.text": "Although the Da Vinci house is now an international luxury watch brand, renowned for watches inspired by iconic paintings, we remain faithful to our founder‚Äôs vision.<BR><BR>As Alessandro Morelli, current president of the Da Vinci Foundation, notes:<BR>‚ÄúThe world changes, but authenticity must never follow fashion. <BR>It is fashion that should follow authenticity.‚Äù<BR><BR>Each Da Vinci collection is conceived as a gallery of watchmaking art: a space where art meets time, where each watch tells a unique story, and where every detail reflects the precise gesture of a master watchmaker.<BR><BR>We collaborate with contemporary artists, art historians, and watchmaking engineers to create unique pieces of haute horlogerie: watches that do not merely measure time, but express it as a work of art.",
      "histoire.section5.text": "On this page, we open the doors to the Da Vinci universe, a world where luxury watchmaking meets artistic creation.<BR>Here, the colors of a painting become the nuances of watch dials, the texture of a canvas inspires handcrafted engravings, and museum light reflects on hand‚Äëpolished cases.<BR><BR>To enrich your immersive experience and reflect our watchmaking expertise, each text is accompanied by:<BR>‚Ä¢\tillustrations of historic workshops, witnesses to our artisanal heritage,<BR>‚Ä¢\tanimations inspired by the movement of the brush, recalling artistic precision,<BR>‚Ä¢\tvisual effects that evoke time, highlighting the poetry and excellence of each watch.<BR><BR>Discover the unique alliance between haute horlogerie, artistic design, and sensory experience at the heart of every Da Vinci creation.",
      "histoire.section6.text": "Visit our Da Vinci boutiques and discover the unique world of luxury watchmaking.<BR>To explore our collections of prestige watches, handle our works of watchmaking art, or simply feel the spirit of the Da Vinci house, we invite you to step into one of our official Da Vinci boutiques.<BR><BR>Here:<BR>‚Ä¢\tart meets time,<BR>‚Ä¢\twatchmaking heritage comes alive,<BR>‚Ä¢\teach luxury watch becomes a sensory and artistic experience.<BR><BR>Discover a space where haute horlogerie blends with artistic creation, and where every visit immerses you in the heart of Da Vinci craftsmanship.",
      "histoire.boutiques": "OUR BOUTIQUES",

